<div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent"><br />There is no need for a "BWA". BEQ or BCS (depending on how you're incrementing the number) will work just fine.<br /></div><br /><br />Put another way, BWA already exists, just as BLT (signed branch if less than) and BGE (signed branch if greater than or equal); they're just spelled differently in an assembler (BEQ/BCS, BCC, and BCS).<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=17">blargg</a> — Sat Oct 29, 2005 6:06 pm</p><hr />
